WEBVTT

NOTE
English visual-description track for the silent GPT-Voice product walkthrough.

00:00.000 --> 00:15.000
Visual: A prompt draft fills with missing goals, context, constraints, examples, success criteria, output format, ambiguity, grammar mistakes, filler, repetition, slow typing, translation detours, and failed recognition.

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
Visual: GPT-Voice appears beside the draft with Transcribe, Retry, Translate, and Prettify actions.

00:19.000 --> 00:29.000
Visual: The Command Dock records a prompt with F9, stops with F10, processes the recording, copies the result, and pastes a prompt draft.

00:29.000 --> 00:38.000
Visual: Recognition fails. Ctrl+F8 resends the same stored audio without a new recording and returns a copied result.

00:38.000 --> 00:45.000
Visual: A Russian voice input is translated into an English prompt with F11. All displayed text remains English.

00:45.000 --> 00:52.000
Visual: F12 removes grammar errors, repetition, and filler from a rough prompt while preserving its meaning.

00:52.000 --> 00:57.000
Visual: ChatGPT Web and OpenAI API are shown as available transcription routes. Provider limits remain visible with the ChatGPT Web claim.

00:57.000 --> 01:00.000
Visual: The final poster resolves to Speak, Retry, Translate, Refine, Better prompts, Less effort, and GPT-Voice on GitHub.
